prevention, and law enforcement support. Chaotic disruptions of
grant funds leave the boots on the ground in a lurch, undermine
the goals of the grant programs, and attack national security.
Republicans who doubt the impact of the grant funding freeze
memo would do well to reach out to their State and local govern-
ments and first responders and ask them about the impact of Don-
ald Trump’s threat to take away DHS funding.
The grant funding freeze means that State and local govern-
ments and first responders may not get reimbursed for the millions
they have already spent to protect and support our communities—
dollars promised to them by the Federal Government. At a min-
imum, the payments will be delayed—and communities cannot af-
ford to go months or years without being paid back due to a dis-
organized and shoddy memo from Donald Trump—nor should they
have to.
The DHS grants that are under threat by the Trump administra-
tion are ones that this Committee has supported in a bipartisan
fashion for years. Every Member of Congress should be alarmed
that—with a push of a button, without even a conversation or let-
ter to Congress—the Trump administration is undermining support
for first responders back home.
Democrats on this Committee are committed to safeguarding na-
tional security, but regrettably, by adversely reporting H. Res. 114,
Committee Republicans have stopped our efforts to conduct effec-
tive oversight of the Trump administration’s chaotic disruptions of
grant funds.
